<TITLE> Rampage for power outage during WC match </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 12 (bdnews24.com)  Load-shedding during a World Cup match between Argentina and Nigeria caused local youths to go on a rampage on the streets at Jatrabari. This led to a long traffic gridlock when the violent youths began to vandalise cars on the streets. Jatrabari police chief Mohammad Moniruzzaman told bdnews24.com that power went out at around 8pm at different areas including Golapbagh, Swamibagh and Gopibagh areas. "At this time a number of youths took to the streets and vandalised a number of cars on the highway. They even threw brickbats at the neighbouring houses." The situation quieted down once power was restored within about a half hour
